England Makes 75-0 Against India on First Day of Cricket Test Before Rain

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-08-18T16:54:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/england-wins-toss-bats-first-against-india-in-the-fourth-cricket-test.html
England  reached 75 for no loss on
the first day of the fourth and final cricket Test against  India 
today. Rain meant no play was possible after lunch.  Captain  Andrew Strauss , who won the toss, has 38 runs, with
 Alastair Cook  on 34 at the Oval in  London . Only 26 overs were
bowled.  England leads the four-match series 3-0.  Bowler  James Anderson  will play for the hosts, having
earlier been in doubt through injury.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  